<HEADLINE>
<P>
WOMEN IN MEN'S LOCKER ROOMS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
As an old male chauvinist, the article by Lutdke caused me a pain in my limited 
thinking processes. 
</P>
<P>
Since I have been consistently pro-choice on the abortion issue and feel this 
is a gender issue that should be decided by women, I have to believe that the 
right to privacy is valid. 
</P>
<P>
Now we have the locker room issue. Do these athletes have a right to privacy? 
</P>
<P>
You missed the obvious solution to the problem. Throw all of the reporters out 
of the locker rooms -- male and female. Women have many fights to win in the 
battle of the sexes. This one should end in a draw. 
</P>
<P>
GLENN R. YOKUM, Riverside 
</P>
</TEXT>
