<HEADLINE>
<P>
WOMEN IN MEN'S LOCKER ROOMS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
There appear to be three logical alternative to resolve the current controversy 
over women reporters conducting their interviews in the men's locker room. 
</P>
<P>
1. Provide an interview room for all reporters; 2. Install a communications 
system that women can use from outside of the locker room, or 3. Require all 
reporters to disrobe before entering the locker room. 
</P>
<P>
Hopefully, a compromise will be reached before we find Barbara Walters 
interviewing Mike Tyson in the men's room at Los Angeles International Airport! 
</P>
<P>
RICK MEASE, Carpinteria 
</P>
</TEXT>
