<HEADLINE>
<P>
WOMEN IN MEN'S LOCKER ROOMS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
As I read Ludtke's argument, I could see Procrustes smiling in vindication of 
his simple-minded system of achieving equality. 
</P>
<P>
Her approach is Procrustean in its attempt to fit the logic of democracy into 
the domain of biology. 
</P>
<P>
I want to suggest that equal civil rights will not suffer if the sexes remain 
separate in locker rooms. Surely a less juvenile way can be found that allows 
reporters to get sports news on an equal basis. 
</P>
<P>
WILLARD OLNEY, Hesperia 
</P>
