<DOCID> 296091 </DOCID>
<DATE>
<P>
October 22, 1990, Monday, Home Edition 
</P>
</DATE>
<SECTION>
<P>
Sports; Part C; Page 15; Column 1; Sports Desk 
</P>
</SECTION>
<LENGTH>
<P>
110 words 
</P>
</LENGTH>
<HEADLINE>
<P>
OVERTIME GOAL KEYS UCLA WIN OVER WAKE FOREST 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Freshman Joe-Max Moore's goal in the seventh minute of overtime Sunday sparked 
third-ranked UCLA to a 2-0 victory over Wake Forest for the championship of the 
sixth annual UCLA-Met Life Classic soccer tournament. 
</P>
<P>
The shot by midfielder Moore from 15 yards in front of the goal came after the 
teams were scoreless in regulation. Freshman Sean Henderson's header in the 
100th minute provided the final goal. 
</P>
<P>
UCLA improved to 13-1-3. Wake Forest fell to 8-6-2. 
</P>
<P>
Moore, who had three assists in the Bruins' 3-0 victory over Air Force Friday 
night, was named the tournament's offensive most valuable player. Wake Forest's 
Craig Conger was defensive MVP. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Game Story 
</P>
</TYPE>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA102290-0028 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 296092 </DOCID>
<DATE>
<P>
October 22, 1990, Monday, Home Edition 
</P>
</DATE>
<SECTION>
<P>
Sports; Part C; Page 18; Column 1; Sports Desk 
</P>
</SECTION>
<LENGTH>
<P>
72 words 
</P>
</LENGTH>
<HEADLINE>
<P>
GOLF; 
</P>
<P>
ANOTHER VICTORY FOR TREVINO 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Lee Trevino made five birdies over the final seven holes Sunday for a 
two-stroke victory over Mike Hill in the $500,000 Transamerica Senior 
Championship at Napa, Calif. 
</P>
<P>
Trevino's seven-under-par 65 earned him $75,000. He finished the 54 holes on 
the 6,632-yard Silverado Country Club south course at 205, 11 under par. 
</P>
<P>
Trevino has now won seven tournaments and $922,352 during his rookie season on 
the PGA Senior Tour. 
</P>
</TEXT>
