<HEADLINE>
<P>
CALIFORNIA IN BRIEF; 
</P>
<P>
OAKLAND; 
</P>
<P>
CHURCH WANTS TO FENCE OFF PROSTITUTES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A congregation wants to put a little separation between its church and the 
state of its neighborhood. St. Andrew's Roman Catholic Church plans to build a 
6-foot-tall, 1,000-foot-long fence around church grounds to keep out 
prostitutes who have been bringing customers there. The Rev. John Maxwell said 
that even his 92-year-old mother has found used condoms and wrappers on the 
steps in front of the rectory where the priests live and in the foliage around 
the church. 
</P>
<P>
"We've always had sporadic prostitution, but now it's gotten way out of hand," 
Maxwell said. Vera Brown, a parishioner who works at the church added: 
"Sometimes they leave clothes, underwear and even stockings out there." Church 
members have raised $8,000 so far to put up the $11,000 fence. 
</P>
</TEXT>
