<HEADLINE>
<P>
CANDIDATE'S OLD WORLD SIGNS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
As more and more political signs appear it becomes increasingly clear that one 
of our Moorpark mayoral candidates has his feet firmly planted on the green 
hills of his Old World birthplace. Is Clint Harper still living, in his heart, 
in those misty isles where the days are soft and where the green hills will 
stay that way because they were hunting preserves owned by the monarch? 
</P>
<P>
This is not a soft land; it is by nature harsh and arid. It becomes green and 
benevolent only when man goes to the time and expense to develop it. And we 
have no monarch who will give us vast tracts of green hills just so we can look 
at them. 
</P>
<P>
Sir, your signs are beautiful and no doubt expensive, but that hill is nowhere 
to be found in Moorpark. 
</P>
<P>
Perhaps I have been unfair. Perhaps that sign is not your Old World birthplace. 
It could be a New World hill. In Patagonia, perhaps? 
</P>
<P>
LINDA SYMCHAK, Moorpark 
</P>
</TEXT>
