<HEADLINE>
<P>
2 CRITICALLY INJURED IN TRUCK ACCIDENT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
One man was near death and a second was in critical condition with head 
injuries at a Ventura hospital Sunday after they were thrown from the bed of a 
pickup truck on California 150 near Lake Casitas. 
</P>
<P>
The driver of the truck and two passengers in the cab left the accident scene 
on foot before officers arrived shortly after 3:30 p.m. Saturday, the 
California Highway Patrol reported. 
</P>
<P>
Esteven Lopez, 30, of Santa Barbara was being kept on life-support systems in 
the intensive care unit at Ventura County Medical Center, a nursing supervisor 
said. 
</P>
<P>
Raoul Teran, 20, of Santa Barbara, suffered major head injuries and was also in 
the hospital's intensive care unit on Sunday. 
</P>
<P>
The two men were airlifted to the hospital following the accident. 
</P>
<P>
A third passenger who was ejected from the truck bed, Juan Echevarria, 17, of 
Santa Barbara, was treated for minor injuries and released, a hospital nurse 
said. 
</P>
<P>
The truck was headed west on California 150 five miles west of Santa Ana Road 
and about five miles east of the Ventura-Santa Barbara County line when the 
truck ran off the road and hit a rock embankment, the CHP said. 
</P>
<P>
Officers did not know the cause of the accident. 
</P>
</TEXT>
