<HEADLINE>
<P>
REDS GET HEARTY WELCOME BACK HOME 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
CINCINNATI 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Hundreds of screaming fans met the Cincinnati Reds' chartered jet Sunday night 
as the World Series champions returned from a four-game sweep of the Oakland 
Athletics. 
</P>
<P>
The crowd of at least 500 cheered as the doors opened after the plane's arrival 
at Greater Cincinnati International Airport. 
</P>
<P>
"It's stirring. It's just overwhelming for all these people to be out here at 
this hour of the night," Reds owner Marge Schott said after emerging from the 
plane to cheers of "Marge! Marge! Marge!" and "Sweep! Sweep! Sweep!" 
</P>
<P>
A downtown parade is planned today. 
