<HEADLINE>
<P>
IN COURT: A SUMMARY OF SOUTHERN CALIFORNIA-RELATED BUSINESS LITIGATION 
DEVELOPMENTS DURING THE PAST WEEK. 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From United Press International 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
'Terminator' Figures Sue Hemdale Film Corp.: Loan-out companies for the star, 
producer, writer and special effects coordinator on the film "The Terminator" 
sued Hemdale Film Corp. and Orion Pictures alleging they breached a contract 
for distribution of profits from the film. The Los Angeles Superior Court 
lawsuit said the film's producer, Gale Anne Hurd, star Arnold Schwarzenegger, 
writer James Cameron and special effects coordinator Stan Winston had 
agreements with Hemdale, which financed the movie, to split profits from the 
film. 
</P>
<P>
The suit said Hemdale breached the agreement by entering into unauthorized 
transactions with other companies, such as Eurofilm Funding Limited, Interlink 
Group and Orbis Communications, and granting them a percentage of the film's 
profits and various fees. The suit seeks unspecified damages and an accounting 
of profits owed. (Case No. BC012873. Filed Oct. 16, 1990). 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Brief; Column; Wire 
</P>
</TYPE>
<SUBJECT>
<P>
THE TERMINATOR (MOTION PICTURE); HEMDALE FILM CORP; BREACH OF CONTRACT; SUITS 
</P>
</SUBJECT>
