<HEADLINE>
<P>
SUSPECT HELD IN GANG SHOOTING 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Service Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
ORANGE 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A man was in custody this morning, booked as a suspect in the fatal 
gang-related shooting of a 20-year-old Corona man, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
Police declined to identify the suspect, saying the investigation is 
continuing. 
</P>
<P>
According to a police account, the victim, Roberto Gonzalez, was walking down 
Tustin Avenue when several men on bicycles approached him. Soon, the group 
began arguing and one suspect pulled a handgun, shooting Gonzalez in the chest, 
police said. Gonzalez was pronounced dead shortly after the shooting at 4 p.m. 
Sunday. Police said they do not know what prompted the argument. 
</P>
