<P>
WHALE BEACHED IN S.F. BAY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
SAN FRANCISCO 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A humpback whale was found beached on mud flats south of Candlestick Park 
today, snarling traffic as commuters on a bayside freeway slowed to watch the 
stranded creature, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
Marine biologists were trying to learn why the whale was stuck in three feet of 
water near the edge of San Francisco Bay, about half a mile south of the 
stadium. The whale may have been the same one seen swimming in the bay south of 
Candlestick on Sunday. 
</P>
<P>
The Coast Guard said it was sending out two boats with biologists from the 
Marine Mammal Center and National Marine Fisheries Service to see if they could 
help the whale. 
</P>
