</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By United Press International 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Stock prices on the Tokyo Stock Exchange surged today as momentum from last 
week's rally boosted the market 2.4%. 
</P>
<P>
The key Nikkei Average of 225 selective issues, which surged 2,091.33 points 
last week including 114.41 points Friday, climbed 589.35 points, or 2.4%, to 
25,070.86. 
</P>
<P>
Volume continued to be stronger than the average of the past several months. An 
estimated 600 million shares changed hands, compared to 1.08 billion shares 
Friday. 
</P>
<P>
Advances topped declines 886 to 133, while 96 issues remained unchanged. 
</P>
<P>
Analysts said lower oil prices and talk of an Iraqi withdrawal from Kuwait drew 
in large financial institutions, which had trailed behind the rally last week. 
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, foreign investors continued to pump funds into the market, they 
said. 
</P>
